with billing_logs_with_list_cost as (
  SELECT
    t1.*,
    t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default as list_cost
  FROM system.billing.usage t1 
  INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices list_prices on
      t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
      t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
      t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
      (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
  WHERE
      t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
      AND (t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' or t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL)
)
SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT usage_metadata.job_id) as jobs,
    COUNT(DISTINCT usage_metadata.notebook_id) as notebooks,
    COUNT(DISTINCT identity_metadata.run_as) as users
from billing_logs_with_list_cost
WHERE usage_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY
GROUP BY ALL

datasets.query:
with billing_logs_with_list_cost as (
  SELECT
    t1.*,
    t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default as list_cost
  FROM system.billing.usage t1 
  INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices list_prices on
      t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
      t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
      t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
      (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
  WHERE
      t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
      AND (t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' or t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL)
)
SELECT
    *
    ,try_divide( (last30DaySpend - last30to60DaySpend) , last30to60DaySpend) * 100 AS Last30DayGrowth
FROM
  (
    SELECT
      SUM(list_cost) AS spend
      ,SUM(CASE WHEN usage_end_time BETWEEN date_add(current_date(), -30) AND current_date() THEN list_cost ELSE 0 END) AS Last30DaySpend
      ,SUM(CASE WHEN usage_end_time BETWEEN date_add(current_date(), -60) AND date_add(current_date(), -31) THEN list_cost ELSE 0 END) AS Last30to60DaySpend
    FROM billing_logs_with_list_cost
    GROUP BY ALL
  )

datasets.name: 543a666e
datasets.query:
-- SPENDING BROKEN DOWN BY JOB
with stats_per_job_run as (
  SELECT
    t1.workspace_id,
    t1.usage_metadata.job_id,
    t1.usage_metadata.job_run_id as run_id,
    SUM(t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default) as list_cost,
    first(identity_metadata.run_as, true) as run_as,
    first(t1.custom_tags, true) as custom_tags,
    MAX(t1.usage_end_time) as last_seen,
    MIN(t1.usage_start_time) as first_seen
  FROM system.billing.usage t1 
  INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices list_prices on
      t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
      t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
      t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
      (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
  WHERE
      t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
      AND t1.usage_metadata.job_id IS NOT NULL
      AND t1.usage_metadata.job_run_id IS NOT NULL
      AND t1.usage_start_time >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY 
  GROUP BY 1,2,3
), 
stats_per_job AS (
  SELECT
    workspace_id,
    job_id,
    COUNT(run_id) AS runs,
    SUM(list_cost) AS total_list_cost,
    AVG(list_cost) AS avg_list_cost,
    MAX(list_cost) AS max_list_cost,
    percentile(list_cost, 0.9) AS p90
  FROM
    stats_per_job_run
  WHERE
    first_seen > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP() - INTERVAL 30 DAYS
  GROUP BY ALL
  ORDER BY
    total_list_cost DESC
)
SELECT
  *,
  (max_list_cost - p90) AS dbus_deviation_from_p90
FROM
  stats_per_job
ORDER BY
  dbus_deviation_from_p90 DESC

datasets.name: 6a78fc9a
datasets.query:
with serverless_logs as (
  SELECT
    t1.*,
    t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default as list_cost
  FROM system.billing.usage t1 
  INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices list_prices on
    t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
    t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
    t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
    (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
  WHERE
    t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
    AND (t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' or t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL)
),
jobs_dollars as (
  select
    date_sub(to_date(usage_date), dayofweek(to_date(usage_date))) as week_start,
    SUM(list_cost) as list_cost,
    COUNT(distinct to_date(usage_start_time)) as days
  from
    serverless_logs t1 
  group by all
  having days = 7
  order by 1 asc, 2 asc
),
dbu_growth as (
    select
        week_start,
        list_cost,
        100 * (list_cost - lag(list_cost, 1) over (order by week_start)) / lag(list_cost, 1) over (order by week_start) as weekly_growth
    from jobs_dollars
    order by week_start asc
)
select
    week_start,
    weekly_growth,
    list_cost,
    avg(weekly_growth) over (order by week_start ROWS BETWEEN 12 preceding AND CURRENT ROW) as 3_months_growth_moving_avg
from dbu_growth

with list_logs as (
    SELECT
        t1.workspace_id,
        identity_metadata.run_as,
        CASE WHEN billing_origin_product = "JOBS" THEN SUM(t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default) ELSE 0 END as `$list_jobs`,
        CASE WHEN billing_origin_product = "NOTEBOOKS" THEN SUM(t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default) ELSE 0 END as `$list_notebooks`
    FROM system.billing.usage t1 
    INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices list_prices on
        t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
        t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
        t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
        (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
    WHERE
        t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
        AND identity_metadata.run_as IS NOT NULL
        AND t1.usage_start_time >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY 
        AND (t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' or t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL)
    GROUP BY workspace_id, run_as, billing_origin_product
)
SELECT 
    *,
    `$list_jobs` + `$list_notebooks` as `$list`
from list_logs
ORDER BY `$list` DESC

datasets.query:
with billing_logs_with_list_cost as (
  SELECT
    t1.*, 
    t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default as list_cost
  FROM system.billing.usage t1 
  INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices list_prices on
    t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
    t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
    t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
    (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
  WHERE 
    (t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' or t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL)
    AND t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
    AND identity_metadata.run_as IS NOT NULL 
    AND usage_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 15 DAY
)
SELECT
    t1.workspace_id
    ,t1.run_as
    ,Last7DaySpend as `Last7Day$list`
    ,Last14DaySpend as `Last14Day$list`
    ,last7DaySpend - last14DaySpend as Last7DayGrowth
    ,try_divide( (last7DaySpend - last14DaySpend) , last14DaySpend) * 100 AS Last7DayGrowthPct
FROM
  (
    SELECT
      workspace_id,
      identity_metadata.run_as,
      SUM(list_cost) AS spend
      ,SUM(CASE WHEN usage_date BETWEEN date_add(current_date(), -8) AND date_add(current_date(), -1) THEN list_cost ELSE 0 END) AS Last7DaySpend
      ,SUM(CASE WHEN usage_date BETWEEN date_add(current_date(), -15) AND date_add(current_date(), -8) THEN list_cost ELSE 0 END) AS Last14DaySpend
    FROM billing_logs_with_list_cost
    GROUP BY ALL
  ) t1 
ORDER BY 
  Last7DayGrowth DESC 
LIMIT 100

datasets.query:
SELECT
    t1.*,
    list_prices.pricing,
    list_prices.pricing.default as default_pricing,
    t1.usage_quantity * list_prices.pricing.default as list_cost,
    CASE
        WHEN t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' THEN 'JOBS'
        WHEN t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'NOTEBOOKS'
    END as origin
FROM system.billing.usage t1 
INNER JOIN system.billing.list_prices on
    t1.cloud = list_prices.cloud and
    t1.sku_name = list_prices.sku_name and
    t1.usage_start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time and
    (t1.usage_end_time <= list_prices.price_end_time or list_prices.price_end_time is null)
WHERE
    t1.sku_name LIKE '%SERVERLESS%'
    AND (t1.sku_name LIKE '%JOBS%' or t1.usage_metadata.notebook_id IS NOT NULL)

## Tutorial

---

### How to get a job by ID?
1. Copy the job_id
2. Navigate to the correct workspace
3. Paste the job ID in a top search toolbar
4. Press enter

### How to get a notebook by ID?
1. Copy the notebook_id
2. Navigate to the correct workspace
3. Paste the notebook ID in a top search toolbar
4. Press enter

### How to get a job run by ID?
1. Follow the *How to get a job by ID?* section
2. Copy run ID
3. Open *any run* on the job runs page
4. Replace the run ID in the url after `/runs/` part
    1. *https://sample-workspace.databricks.com/jobs/123456789/runs/**111213141516***

widget.textbox_spec:
## Serverless Jobs and Notebooks Cost Observability  v0.1

--- 

This dashboard operates on a list cost (**$list**). The list cost is calculated as `number of DBUs * list price per DBU at that moment in time`. Account-specific rates and discounts are not included. We will be evolving it over time by adding more example queries and visualizations, helping you keep track of spending on Serverless Jobs and Notebooks. For the latest version checkout documentation and GitHub link below.

#### Documentation 
- [Serverless Notebooks](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/databricks/compute/serverless)
- [Serverless Jobs](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/databricks/workflows/jobs/run-serverless-jobs)
- [TODO: Latest Dashboard version GitHub]()

#### Requirements
- This dashboard requires **system.usage** System Table
    - [How to Enable System Table Schema](https://docs.databricks.com/en/administration-guide/system-tables/index.html#enable-system-table-schemas)
    - [Grant access to system tables](https://docs.databricks.com/en/administration-guide/system-tables/index.html#grant-access-to-system-tables)

#### Feedback
Please use the [following form](https://surveys.training.databricks.com/jfe/form/SV_6MeRdfngaqxqzum) to provide feedback on this dashboard & serverless jobs and notebooks cost observability.

#### Debugging
For detailed debugging instructions (how to find job/notebook/run by ID) check out the guidance at the bottom of this dashboard.
